{"word":"ἵστωρ","slug":"ἵστωρ","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἵστωρ</b></el> <el>(ἵστωρ, ορος,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:οἶδα'><el>οἶδα</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a wise man, one who knows right, a judge</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>as <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a> <i>knowing</i>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>; <el>ἵστωρ τινός</el> <i>knowing</i> a thing, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}